h3.
 What am I looking at?
p.
 Cerfer.us provides 24 hours of the most current surf forecast data from Magic Seaweed, repackaged and animated to illustrate a map level overview.
h3.
 How do I read this map?
p.
 Each colored circle on the map represents a beach in the MSW database.
p The color of the beach marker represents the swell quality/power.
  div
    div(ng-repeat="color in colors" class="info-circle" ng-style="{'background': '{{color}}'}")
  div 
    span(class="weak") weak
    span(class="strong") strong
p The length, speed and orientation of the yellow vectors represent wind speed and direction. (Below is a 5mph NW wind)
  div(class="info-wind-container")

h3 What can I infer from this map?
p Generally speaking, if the circle is dark and wind is light and blowing off-shore, you should probably go paddle out around that vicinity.
